The paper deals with self-stabilizing protocols in distributed systems, which is a topic that falls under the categories of Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing (cs.DC), Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS), Networking and Internet Architecture (cs.NI), Systems and Control (cs.SY), and Information Theory (cs.IT). The paper specifically focuses on message-passing systems, which is a sub-topic of cs.DC and cs.NI. The use of spanning directed acyclic graphs is also a common technique in cs.DS. Therefore, the most likely categories are cs.DC, cs.DS, and cs.NI, followed by cs.SY and cs.IT.
